Here's TUnit's lifecycle at each scope:

## 1. Before/After every test in a class

```csharp
public class OrderTests
{
    [Before(Test)]
    public async Task ResetDatabase(TestContext context)
    {
        await InMemoryDb.ResetAsync();
    }

    [After(Test)]
    public async Task Cleanup(TestContext context)
    {
        // runs after each test
    }

    [Test]
    public async Task Order_WithNoItems_Throws() { /* ... */ }
}
```

You can also use a constructor and/or `IAsyncDisposable.DisposeAsync`.

---

## 2. Once per class (class-scoped fixture)

```csharp
public class CustomerApiTests
{
    private static HttpClient _client = null!;

    [Before(Class)]
    public static async Task StartFixture(ClassHookContext context)
    {
        _client = new HttpClient { BaseAddress = new Uri("http://localhost:5000") };
    }

    [After(Class)]
    public static async Task DisposeFixture(ClassHookContext context)
    {
        _client.Dispose();
    }

    [Test]
    public async Task GetCustomer_Returns200() { /* ... */ }
}
```

These methods must be **static**.

---

## 3. Once per assembly

```csharp
public class WireMockHook
{
    [Before(Assembly)]
    public static async Task StartWireMock(AssemblyHookContext context)
    {
        // start in-process WireMock server
    }

    [After(Assembly)]
    public static async Task StopWireMock(AssemblyHookContext context)
    {
        // stop server
    }
}
```

The class can live anywhere in the assembly — TUnit discovers it automatically.

---

## 4. Once per entire test session

```csharp
public class GlobalDatabaseHook
{
    [Before(TestSession)]
    public static async Task ApplyMigrations(TestSessionContext context)
    {
        await Database.MigrateAsync();
    }

    [After(TestSession)]
    public static async Task TearDown(TestSessionContext context)
    {
        await Database.DropAsync();
    }
}
```

---

## Quick-reference table

| Scope | Before | After |
|-------|--------|-------|
| Each test | `[Before(Test)]` | `[After(Test)]` |
| Class | `[Before(Class)]` (static) | `[After(Class)]` (static) |
| Assembly | `[Before(Assembly)]` (static) | `[After(Assembly)]` (static) |
| Session | `[Before(TestSession)]` (static) | `[After(TestSession)]` (static) |

**Bonus:** `[BeforeEvery(Test)]` / `[AfterEvery(Test)]` (and `Class`/`Assembly` variants) are global cross-cutting hooks that fire for *every* test/class regardless of which class they're declared in — handy for logging or diagnostics.

All hooks support `async Task`, an optional context parameter, and an optional `CancellationToken`.
